This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump and President Xi during a meeting in Buenos Aires. President Trump expressed his appreciation for President Xi's condolences to the Bush family following the passing of President George H.W. Bush. They discussed various topics including the fentanyl problem in the US, trade, and the China-US relationship. President Trump expressed his optimism for a positive outcome that would benefit both countries. President Xi emphasized the importance of cooperation between China and the US for world peace and prosperity. President Trump also mentioned that Air Force One would be used to transport President Bush's casket from Houston to Washington.